codex
I’ve got enough to write the report. The strongest findings are not style issues: header hashes are wrong for ordinary nonzero integer fields, Prague requests commitments are computed with the wrong algorithm, and the public block factory accepts transaction-shaped data but stores it as non-transaction objects.
